  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Transfontanellar Doppler can measure the velocity at both the carotid artery and the anterior
      cerebral artery during cardiopulmonary bypass in congenital heart disease patients. This
      study can provide reference value of appropriate cerebral blood flow velocity during
      pediatric cardiac surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
